rap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/bknightsoffreedom94013.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jurgen>Jurgen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Squire</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FFFCCC>(3/25/02 8:02:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fknightsoffreedom94013frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /hitsmod</span><hr size=1> I will be first to admit I am a plug and pray kinda guy. I dont get the new hits mod at all if anyone has any suggestions please post them to help rest of us. Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=555555><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/ucharcoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Charcoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Marshal of the March</span><br>  Posts: 646<br> <font color=#FFFCCC>(3/25/02 8:16:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fknightsoffreedom94013frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /hitsmod</span><hr size=1> Great new feature. Very non-intuitive interface. Here's what I've learned in my experimentation.<br>
<br>
Usage: /hitsmode &lt;my|me|other&gt; &lt;on|off|m2|m3|m4|m5&gt; &lt;X&gt; &lt;Y&gt; &lt;COUNT&gt; &lt;FONTSIZE&gt; &lt;HEADER&gt; &lt;BG&gt; &lt;WIDTH&gt; &lt;FORCEDRAW&gt;<br>
<br>
Example (I use this):<br>
/hitsmode my m5 550 450 7 1 1 1 100 0<br>
/hitsmode me on<br>
/histmode other off<br>
<br>
You can have up to 3 separate additional windows, one for MY hits on mobs, one for things hitting ME, and one for OTHER folks' hits. I like having the separate window for my hits since I attack very fast and miss a lot otherwise. I turn others' hits off because I'd go LD on a raid otherwise. I like things hitting me in the main window, because it's big and red and I know I better do something about it when I see it.<br>
<br>
Here's an explanation of the various parameters I use for the MY window:<br>
<br>
550 450: XY coordinates for where the window starts. I don't know what measurement is being used, pixels maybe? This puts the window within my text box, but to the right of most text that scrolls by.<br>
<br>
7: 7 lines of text appear at a time.<br>
<br>
1: Fontsize of 1 is good for me. 0 is way tiny, anything bigger takes too much room.<br>
<br>
1: I like having the box say 'My hits' for some reason.<br>
<br>
1: I like the shaded box. Not for everyone.<br>
<br>
100: The pixel width (I guess) of the shaded box.<br>
<br>
0: If this is 1, the shaded box with header stays up all the time. If 0, it hides the box when not being used.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now my magician alt needs to see what's going on with his pet's attacks, and mostly solos, so he puts up an OTHER window as well, usually at the top of the screen. But in a raid situation or even just a group, this is an invitation to go LD... too much information.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps. <p><a target=new href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=97778>Charcoth Caranson</a><br>Ranger of Karana in his 53rd Season<br>Knights of Freedom<br>Brell Serilis<br><br><center><img src=http://EQbubbles.homestead.com/files/Charcoth.jpg> <a/><center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=444444><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub66.ezboard.com/uchanterin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chanterin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_star.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchantress Extraodinaire</span><br>  Posts: 500<br> <font color=#FFFCCC>(3/26/02 12:16:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub66.ezboard.com/fknightsoffreedom94013frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=570.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /hitsmod</span><hr size=1> Sounds GREAT!<br>
